  Design Document: Batch Processing System
Objective
Automate the execution of multiple COT analysis runs based on a configuration file (
user_input/batching.csv
), ensuring each run uses specific settings and saves results to a unique, non-overwriting folder.

Proposed Architecture
1. 
main.py
 CLI Overrides
Enhance 
main.py
 to accept CLI arguments that override any settings in 
user_config.csv
 or 
instruments.csv
.

--instrument [name]: Filter the processing list to only this instrument name. Force enabled=True for this name.
--range [START:END]: Override the chart display range (clipped x-axis).
--tag [string]: Set a custom research tag for folder naming.
2. Output Folder Suffixing
Update the configuration loader to automatically generate a unique output path for charts.

Path Pattern: output/charts/res_[tag]_[range]/
Example: output/charts/res_v1_20000101-20050101/
This ensures that batch runs don't overwrite each other's image files.
3. Batch Runner Tool: tools/run_batch.py
A new script dedicated to orchestration.

Input: Reads 
user_input/batching.csv
.
Logic:
Iterates through each investigation row.
Performs string normalization (e.g., converting en-dashes – and hyphens - to a standard format) to reliably link 
batching.csv
 names to 
instruments.csv
 records.
Spawns a subprocess for each run: python main.py --instrument "GC - Gold" --range "01-01-2001:31-12-2005" --tag "v1"
Reporting: Logs the success/failure of each batch item.
Normalization Strategy
To handle names like GC – Gold (en-dash) vs GC - Gold (hyphen):

Convert to lowercase.
Replace all punctuation/dashes with a single space.
Strip leading/trailing whitespace.
Result for both: gc gold.
